            </span>

            </span>
           </b>
           : There are plenty of features I'm working on for the new Urban Terror, but not many are that interesting or visual. That, combined with the fact that writing blog posts takes quite a bit of time, is the reason why you see me so rarely post updates of the progress I'm doing on the game. Recently, I've implemented the crosshairs for Resurgence and that is something worth writing about.  So, let's co […]

         <div class="darkerBox" id="news_520_520">
          <div class="rightIcon">
           <img border="0" src="data:image/png;base64,"/>
          </div>
          <div class="textheader">
           <h3>
            <img alt="newspaper" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="newspaper"/>
            Urban Terror 4.3.4 release
           </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="textinfo">
           <img alt="bullet_none" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="visitor"/>
           <i>
            in
            <a href="/news/cats/urt/">
             Urban Terror
            </a>
            - posted
            <span title="Thu, 21 Jun 2018 23:14:00 +0200 GMT">
             1 month ago
            </span>
            by
            <span class="userOrg">
             FrozenSand
            </span>
           </i>
          </div>
          <div class="textcontent">
           <img align="right" alt="" border="0" class="intext right" onload="img_checker(this);" src="/cache/images/texts/news/516.1.png"/>
           <br/>
           Although we make the best effort to ensure the stability of our releases, a bug occurring on very rare occasions fell under our radar in the 4.3.3 release.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           The 4.3.4 release should fix this bug, which would induce random game crashes and freezes on specific maps (especially Eagle).
           <br/>
           <br/>
           To update your game client, simply run the UrTUpdater executable from your game folder. You can alternatively
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tcvLUpKzCtJLSrKL9LLzEvL10_JL8_LyU9MKdZXyICqKS8v18NQl5Gfm6oPAA" target="_blank">
            download
           </a>
           the full Urban Terror 4.3.4 pack or the 4.3.3 to 4.3.4 update package.
           <div class="noteBox noteInformation">
            <span class="title">
             Information:
            </span>
            This release contains several important security fixes as well as various bug fixes and improvements. It is highly recommended to update as soon as possible.
           </div>
           <a name="A">
           </a>
           <h3 class="bbcode">
            Changelog
           </h3>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the random crash issues which happened especially (but not only) on the map Eagle
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3MTZUyIDqKi8v1ysFqSkBq9HLzEvL18_Iz03VBwA" target="_blank">
             #431
            </a>
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed several potential buffer overflow exploits
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the bug where unpinning a 2nd nade in a row and switching to another weapon would result in the nade being dropped on the floor.
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3MlPIgGoqLy_XKwUpKQEr0cvMS8vXz8jPTdUHAA" target="_blank">
             #26
            </a>
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed players being stuck with level 19 in Gun Game when g_randomorder was set to 1
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3MTZTyIDqKi8v1ysFqSkBq9HLzEvL18_Iz03VBwA" target="_blank">
             #436
            </a>
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Magnum: fixed the reload animation and the reappearance of the crosshair not being completely synced
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Bomb mode: fixed SurvivorWinner events not being written in the server logs in some situations.
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3sjRWyIDqKi8v1ysFqSkBq9HLzEvL18_Iz03VBwA" target="_blank">
             #293
            </a>
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            In order to free up some space in the "serverinfo" variable, and to try to prevent the "info string length exceeded" error messages on the servers, and the subsequent potential bugs:
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             1
            </span>
            Removed g_bombDefuseTime and g_bombExplodeTime from the serverinfo
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             2
            </span>
            Changed g_teamnameRed and g_teamnameBlue to g_nameRed and g_nameBlue
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             3
            </span>
            Removed the "Clan" and "Location" serverinfo vars from server_example.cfg - server admins are free to add them back to their configs if needed
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             4
            </span>
            Removed auth_tags, auth_verbosity, auth_cheaters and auth_log from the serverinfo as they weren't strictly needed
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             5
            </span>
            Removed dmflags from the serverinfo string, it's an unused leftover from Quake 2
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum listnum">
             6
            </span>
            This frees up about 115 chars in the serverinfo string
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed output of the "where" client command
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed map/next map vote menu ignoring previously highlighted map and calling vote with the first map on the list
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3NDJSyIDqKi8v1ysFqSkBq9HLzEvL18_Iz03VBwA" target="_blank">
             #122
            </a>
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Menus: fixed inconsistencies in leading space in weapon select screen.
            <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLdY3NjBRyIDqKi8v1ysFqSkBq9HLzEvL18_Iz03VBwA" target="_blank">
             #304
            </a>
           </div>
           <a name="B">
           </a>
           <h3 class="bbcode">
            Updated engine
           </h3>
           Thanks to an incredible community effort led by
           <a href="/external-link/?r=ZcvBDYAgDAXQVZyAf9ZtgJS0kVJSMF3fizff_fHec13A4yWPTe7mSUYzKGkhX5huTTpBpd6Z-omDvxIR6dfYlPAC" target="_blank">
            mickael9
           </a>
           , you are now able to play Urban Terror 4.3 on an engine which is up to date with the latest
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tfPzC8sTcxONdbLL0pXyIAKlpeX65UWJSXmlaQWFeUX6WXmpeXrZ-TnpuoDAA" target="_blank">
            ioquake3
           </a>
           features. This engine brings support for VoIP, Mumble, a new OpenGL2 renderer, and fixes hundreds of engine bugs along the way.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           If you wish to try this new engine version (
           <strong class="emphasis">
            currently in beta
           </strong>
           ), please open your UrTUpdater, go to File -&gt; Settings and select the "ioq3-m9" engine.
           <a name="C">
           </a>
           <h3 class="bbcode">
            Thank you!
           </h3>
           Many thanks to the players who have reported issues on our
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLVbIgOooLy_XKwXJl4Dl9TLz0vL1M_JzU_UB" target="_blank">
            GitHub repository
           </a>
           . We would also like to say a special thank you to the
           <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/groups/profile/dn/">
            DrunkNoobs
           </a>
           clan as well as
           <a href="/external-link/?r=ZcvBDYAgDAXQVZyAf9ZtgJS0kVJSMF3fizff_fHec13A4yWPTe7mSUYzKGkhX5huTTpBpd6Z-omDvxIR6dfYlPAC" target="_blank">
            mickael9
           </a>
           and
           <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/members/profile/ttimo/">
            TTimo
           </a>
           for their help with debugging the game crash issue.
           <div class="noteBox noteMisc bblast">
            <span class="title">
             comments:
            </span>
            Feel free to discuss this on our
            <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/forums/topic/35195-urban-terror-434-release/">
             forums
            </a>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="textmenu">
           <span>
            <img alt="link" class="icon small" src="data:image/png;base64," title="link"/>
            <a href="http://www.urbanterror.info/news/520-urban-terror-4-3-4-release/">
             link
            </a>
           </span>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="darkerBox" id="news_519_519">
          <div class="rightIcon">
           <img border="0" src="data:image/png;base64,"/>
          </div>
          <div class="textheader">
           <h3>
            <img alt="newspaper" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="newspaper"/>
            Coming soon: Urban Terror 4.3.4 release
           </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="textinfo">
           <img alt="bullet_none" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="visitor"/>
           <i>
            in
            <a href="/news/cats/urt/">
             Urban Terror
            </a>
            - posted
            <span title="Fri, 08 Jun 2018 15:49:00 +0200 GMT">
             1 month ago
            </span>
            by
            <span class="userOrg">
             FrozenSand
            </span>
           </i>
          </div>
          <div class="textcontent">
           <div class="noteBox noteEdit bbfirst">
            <span class="title">
             Edit:
            </span>
            <b>
             Urban Terror 4.3.4 will be released this Thursday, June 21st in the evening.
            </b>
           </div>
           <center class="intext">
            <img align="center" alt="" border="0" class="intext center" onload="img_checker(this);" src="/cache/images/texts/news/519.1.png"/>
           </center>
           <br/>
           The Urban Terror 4.3.4 release will include some important bug fixes regarding the game's stability and security. The crash issues on some maps and servers were especially tricky to tackle but they should now be fixed.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           In order to confirm the bug fixes, a pre-release of UrT 4.3.4 is available now for testing:
           <br/>
           <br/>
           <span style="font-size: 149%">
            <b>
             <div style="text-align: center;">
              <center>
               <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/forums/topic/35191-urban-terror-434-release-candidate-1/">
                Urban Terror 4.3.4 Pre-Release #1 thread
               </a>
              </center>
             </div>
            </b>
           </span>
           <div class="noteBox noteWarning">
            <span class="title">
             Warning:
            </span>
            This pre-release is to be used for testing purpose only, do
            <b>
             NOT
            </b>
            use it for regular/competitive play!
           </div>
           Please visit the forum thread for information on how to download and install the test build. Several servers with various gametypes are available for testing.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Your feedback is welcome!
           <div class="noteBox noteMisc bblast">
            <span class="title">
             comments:
            </span>
            Feel free to discuss this on our
            <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/forums/topic/35191-urban-terror-434-release-candidate-1/">
             forums
            </a>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="textmenu">
           <span>
            <img alt="link" class="icon small" src="data:image/png;base64," title="link"/>
            <a href="http://www.urbanterror.info/news/519-coming-soon-urban-terror-4-3-4/">
             link
            </a>
           </span>
          </div>
         </div>

           </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="textinfo">
           <img alt="bullet_none" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="visitor"/>
           <i>
            in
            <a href="/news/cats/leagues/">
             Leagues
            </a>
            - posted
            <span title="Mon, 07 May 2018 22:01:00 +0200 GMT">

            </span>

          </div>
          <div class="textcontent">
           The Urban Zone League is pleased to announce that it is organizing a 2vs2 Cup; the DreamStars!
           <br/>
           <br/>
           <iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="283" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/F2-8onvI_8I" width="504">
           </iframe>
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Urban Zone is proud to invite you starting on Sunday, May 13th. Everyone is invited to participate and try to win the prize!
           <br/>
           <br/>
           The tournament will span several weeks with a variety of maps. To participate, it is necessary that you are using an Urban Terror AUTH account and that you are registered on the Urban Zone website. For this first edition of the DreamStars 2vs2 Cup, the League will offer 50€ for the winning team and 20€ for the second place.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           If you have any questions or inquiries, you're very welcome to join the league on its
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPySxOzi9K0UtP1zfICnApDoq0SHP3d3FLLsxWyICqKS8v1ystSkrMK0ktKsov0svMS8vXz8jPTdUHAA" target="_blank">
            Discord
           </a>
           or Teamspeak (ts.urban-terror.fr) servers, feel free to ask the admins anything you want.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Have Fun!

          <div class="textcontent">
           Dear players,
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Like flowers, competition on UrT is back!
           <br/>
           <center class="intext">
            <a href="/cache/images/texts/news/517.1.png" onclick="show_popup('/cache/images/texts/news/517.1.png'); return false;" target="_BLANK">
             <img align="center" alt="" border="0" class="intext center" src="/cache/images/texts/news/517.1.2.png"/>
            </a>
           </center>
           <br/>
           It is with huge pleasure that the Urban Zone league announces the new competition; even including a Cash Prize for the sunny Spring Cup this time. The rules will be the same as the Winter Cup and game modes will be the same as last time for both cups (Pro &amp; Fun).
           <br/>
           <br/>
           The best 8 teams of the Fun Cup will join the Pro Cup to have the possibility to win the so desired Cash prize!
           <br/>
           <br/>

            here
           </a>
           for the Fun Cup.
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Pro Cup and Fun Cup will start Monday 23rd of April so be ready!
           <br/>
           <br/>
           Click
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPySxOzi9K0UtP1zfICnApDoq0SHP3d3FLLsxWyICqKS8v1ystSkrMK0ktKsov0svMS8vXz8jPTdUHAA" target="_blank">
            here
           </a>
           to join the Urban Zone Discord server.

         <div class="darkerBox" id="news_516_516">
          <div class="rightIcon">

          <div class="textheader">
           <h3>
            <img alt="newspaper" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="newspaper"/>
            Urban Terror 4.3.3 release
           </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="textinfo">
           <img alt="bullet_none" class="icon" src="data:image/png;base64," title="visitor"/>
           <i>
            in
            <a href="/news/cats/urt/">
             Urban Terror
            </a>
            - posted
            <span title="Wed, 28 Feb 2018 23:15:05 +0100 GMT">
             Wednesday, 28 February 2018
            </span>
            by
            <span class="userOrg">
             FrozenSand
            </span>
           </i>
          </div>
          <div class="textcontent">
           <center class="intext">
            <img align="center" alt="" border="0" class="intext center" onload="img_checker(this);" src="/cache/images/texts/news/516.2.png"/>
           </center>
           <br/>
           <div style="text-align: center;">
            <center>
             <i>
              Bugs squashed!
             </i>
            </center>
           </div>
           <br/>
           <br/>
           While the development team is working hard on Urban Terror Resurgence with the goal to bring it to your screens quickly, we have cooked a 4.3.3 release for Urban Terror : Still Dying.
           <div class="noteBox noteInformation">
            <span class="title">
             Information:
            </span>
            This release contains several important security fixes and various bug fixes and improvements. It is highly recommended to update as soon as possible.
           </div>
           To update your game client, simply run the UrTUpdater executable from your game folder. You can alternatively download the full Urban Terror 4.3.3 pack or the 4.3.2 to 4.3.3 update package.
           <a name="A">
           </a>
           <h3 class="bbcode">
            Changelog
           </h3>
           <a name="A.1">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Security fixes
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed CVE-2017-6903 #73
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a potential buffer overflow exploit with the funstuff cvars
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a potential exploit with the cl_guid variable
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a potential exploit: do not allow loading .menu files from the /download/ subfolder and enforce menu files to have the .menu extension
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a potential exploit where the result of the /stats command called by a spectator while following a player would be sent to the followed player instead of the spectator
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a potential exploit with ROM and INIT cvar types being forced to USERINFO
           </div>
           <a name="A.2">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Engine
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the server browser not showing any server when using the legacy Quake 3 engine
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed modern ioq3 engines crashing with the error "Engine linkage error #31" #399
           </div>
           <a name="A.3">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Match Mode
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the substitute status being sometimes applied when g_matchmode = 0 #404
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed substitute players randomly spawning and being invincible on map restart in certain game modes
           </div>
           <a name="A.4">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Jump Mode
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed wrong value of y-axis being used when loading a saved position in Jump mode #80
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Jump mode: fixed persistent position saving which was sometimes loading another player's saved position #131
           </div>
           <a name="A.5">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Gameplay
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Gun Game: fixed being stuck with the HK69 when playing with g_randomorder 1 #394
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Tweaked the FR-F1: torso/vest hits make players bleed. Zoom reset if getting &gt;= 50% of damage (previously: 20%)
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Tweaked P90's and Benelli's positions on screen #217
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Potentially fixed fire mode of a spectated player's weapon being sometimes picked up #7
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed bots failing to load on Cascade and Kingdom
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Tweaked bot files for UrT 4.3.3
           </div>
           <a name="A.6">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Rcon
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed g_inactivity timer inconsistencies #414
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the rcon "players" command that wasn't always displaying player's auth names #419
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed /rcon players command returning wrong slot and IP values for clients
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Added current half info to /rcon players if g_swaproles is set to 1
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a bug where a map_restart after changing the g_matchmode cvar would spawn the same random weapon an infinite number of times #81
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed g_redteamlist and g_blueteamlist not always being recognized as valid server cvars #83
           </div>
           <a name="A.7">
           </a>
           <h4 class="bbcode">
            Miscellaneous
           </h4>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Potentially fixed the "Couldn't find weapon xx" error which was introduced in 4.2.014
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the TOD50 texture file size which was causing a crash on map load when using the legacy Quake 3 engine
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Updated quake3's master server port in server_example.cfg (please update your custom server configs!)
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed the server browser showing several times the same servers when quickly refreshing the list multiple times
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Clarified server browser filter options
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed a bug where spamming a key binding while downloading a map would result in a "client overflow" game crash
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Fixed ignore list not being saved on map reload/change and other inconsistencies with the /ignore command #23
           </div>
           <div class="ordernum">
            <span class="ordernum">
             •
            </span>
            Replaced all .png textures with .tga textures to fix some UI elements not being displayed correctly when using the legacy Quake 3 engine
           </div>
           <br/>
           Many thanks to the players who have reported issues on our
           <a href="/external-link/?r=yygpKSi20tdPzyzJKE3SS87P1Xcryq9KzQtOzEvRDy1KSswLSS0qyi8y0c8sLi5NLVbIgOooLy_XKwXJl4Dl9TLz0vL1M_JzU_UB" target="_blank">
            GitHub repository
           </a>
           , as well as community developers who contributed to the engine code, menus files and bot files: Ionkamikaze, IyeOnline, mickael9, NotVeryGood, Z3nny and travmon.
           <div class="noteBox noteMisc bblast">
            <span class="title">
             comments:
            </span>
            Feel free to discuss this on our
            <a href="https://www.urbanterror.info/forums/topic/35130-urban-terror-433-release/">
             forums
            </a>
           </div>
          </div>

           <span>
            <img alt="link" class="icon small" src="data:image/png;base64," title="link"/>
            <a href="http://www.urbanterror.info/news/516-urban-terror-4-3-3-release/">
             link
            </a>
           </span>
          </div>
         </div>

          </div>
